## Limitations

The findings are based on current research, which is still evolving. The understanding of COVID-19 immunity is incomplete, and ongoing studies may provide new insights. Additionally, the variability in individual health conditions and environmental factors can influence susceptibility, making it challenging to generalize findings across populations. Further research is needed to fully understand the mechanisms behind natural immunity and resistance to COVID-19.